# Quality Guidelines

## Security

- Use Better Auth for authentication; validate all inputs via `@ziron/validators`.
- Rate limiting via `@ziron/rate-limit` on oRPC and public routes.
- Store sensitive data in env vars; never in code.

## Accessibility

- Follow WCAG 2.1 AA; use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`).
- Provide alt text for images; ensure keyboard navigation.
- Use ARIA labels when semantic HTML isn't sufficient.

## Error Handling

- **Client:** Error boundaries for route/section-level failures; user-friendly messages.
- **Server:** try/catch with context; return appropriate oRPC error codes (UNAUTHORIZED, NOT_FOUND, etc.).
- Log errors with context (userId, path) for debugging.

## Data Fetching

- Use oRPC procedures (not server actions) for API calls; TanStack Query for client caching.
- Handle loading and error states; use Suspense for streaming where appropriate.
